During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed various topics including the ongoing relief efforts for Hurricanes Irma and Harvey, bipartisan discussions on tax reform, and the President's meeting with Senator Tim Scott. Sanders also mentioned that the President will be hosting a dinner with Senator Schumer and Congresswoman Pelosi to discuss the upcoming legislative agenda, with a focus on tax reform. She also addressed questions about the President's stance on healthcare, the meeting with Senator Scott, and the President's commitment to working with Democrats. Sanders also mentioned that the President will be meeting with Republican and Democrat House members, and that the President is committed to keeping the American Dream alive for all Americans.